NASTRAN SYSTEM(674)=1
$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$
$
$ DESCRIPTION - TEST INVOLVING CDAMP1 AS WELL AS CELAS1 AND CONM1 ELEMENTS.
$               2 NODES ARE CONSIDERED. ONE IS FIXED, THE OTHER IS EXCITED.
$               ONE CONM1 ELEMENT IS DEFINED ON EACH NODE.
$               ONE CELAS1 ELEMENT AND ONE CDAMP1 ELEMENT ARE DEFINED BETWEEN THE TWO NODES.
$               CDAMP1 ELEMENT IS NOT GROUNDED.
$               CELAS1 ELEMENT IS NOT GROUNDED.
$               THE TRANSLATION CASE IS CONSIDERED, CELAS1 AND CDAMP1 ARE DEFINED BETWEEN THE (GLOBAL) Y COMPONENT OF THE FIXED NODE AND THE (LOCAL) Y COMPONENT OF THE EXCITED NODE.
$               LOCAL AXES ARE DEFINED ON THE EXCITED NODE ONLY.
$               THE LOCAL X DIRECTION CORRESPONDS TO THE GLOBAL -Y DIRECTION.
$               THE LOCAL Y DIRECTION CORRESPONDS TO THE GLOBAL -Z DIRECTION.
$               THE LOCAL Z DIRECTION CORRESPONDS TO THE GLOBAL  X DIRECTION.
$               ELEMENT PROPERTIES:
$               MX = MY = MZ = 1 KG ON BOTH SIDES
$               STIFFNESS = 100 N/M
$               VISCOUS DAMPING = 0.5 N.S/M
$
$
